	   <tr><td colspan=2>I forgot to post this in my last message. One trick I like to use with my pet is this. When I was in the low teens, I would solo in the Swamp of No Hope, killing the Iksar Marauders. They have a camp in the Swamp where they're pretty much gathered in a circle. I knew that if I fought one of them, they'd ALL be on me. Here's what I did: after making sure my mana was gtg, I cast a punching bag (pet) and sent him into the very middle of the camp, attacking the marauder in the center. I backed off a good distance from the fight, but still close enough that they'd give chase. As soon as I saw my pet die, I HAULED ASS to the Cabilis gates with about 8 of these guys behind me, and watched the Troopers mutilate them all. Dangerous? heck yeah! BUT the camp was cleared and I EASILY racked up exp by simply picking them off one at a time as each one spawned! I haven't tried this anywhere else, but I'm sure it'd work in other places too. If you are an Iksar, you MIGHT try it in the Overthere, where you got the two Scorpion-Iksar brothers who guard the canyon (FYI these dudes can DESTROY the Sarnak Knights and Berserkers! Saw it with my OWN eyes when they chased ME!). If you can go into the Outpost, I'm sure the Golem and the Goon would do the trick! Give it a try and let me know how it goes!<br><br>Peye<br>28 Iksar Shadowknight<br>Leader, Principles of Pain<br>Tarew Marr Server<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Apr 22 11:55:01 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>... one of the reasons people cling to their hates so stubbornly is because they sense, once the hate is gone, that they will be forced to deal with Pain.<br>-James Baldwin</td></tr>
