	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10192260965748><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=10192260965748>Race?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=10192260965748#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61489><span id=Scholar>Kamlatir, Eater of Souls</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>66 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 19th 10:27 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>For everyone wanting to know what race to pick for their characters, I have an interestin experiment for you. Make an ogre warrior and keep his sta at it's base value. Then make a dwarf warrior and with the help of some crusty get his sta to the same level as the ogres. Watch their hitpoints and you'll see they are the same. Level them both to two and they will still be the same. <br><br>Classes get different amount of hp per sta, races don't. Starting stats are indeed important but when you reach the point where you have 230 plus in all stats a DE will tank just as well as an ogre. Some things don't change of course, troll and iksar regen changes over levels but more dramatically then other races. A level 60 has 6 point per tick regen while a 60 iksar or troll has 16 per tick. So if you think you'll stay in this game for a long time and eventually reach the high end game, go with the look you like the best and feel most comfortable with :)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
