	   <tr><td colspan=2>First off let me make a little apology to the people frequenting these boards: I'm not in the habit of getting into pointless flames and reading my reply to Lunatic I concede that fact that it wasn't totally well formulated. My excuse is that I was a bit grouchy that day and that people that post just for the sake of posting annoy me. <br><br>Short recap:<br><br>Same sta and same class gives the same hp.<br><br>A de with the same stamina as an ogre has the same hp and therefor the same &quot;tanking ability&quot;.<br><br>I state that if you're in it for the long run and aspire to reach the end game choose whatever race you like the most because you'll be able to tank just as well with the gear there.<br><br>Lunatic says no, de has to sacrifice ac for hp or something.<br><br>Using the allakhazam character system I made an Erudite (a race recognized as being weak in the melee stat department) and an ogre. I put 5 into agility for each of them to compensate for the fact that they start with 70 in agi and thereby would incurr an ac penalty. The rest of the starting points went into sta. I then looked for the greatest ac item for every slot and proceeded to add them to the characters. I stopped after adding Chest, Legs, Feet, Arms, Wrist, Hands, Waist, Face and Neck. Reason? I'd added the greatest ac item in those slots and the Ogre was at 255 sta while the erudite was at 240. Add one or two items and the erudite will be at 255 also. With the best ac items, not the best stamina items.<br><br>Point proven. If you think there's anything else except hp and ac that makes up tanking ability please let me know. If you think DE's have terrible melee stats that's fine Lunatic, post it in a separate thread next time since my post was about end game and being satisfied with the visual appearence of your character besides the fact that different races of the same class get the same amount of hp per point of sta.<br><br>Kamlatir,<br>Grave Lord of Far Seekers, The Rathe<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Apr 30 19:09:38 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
