	   <tr><td colspan=2>Guys--I think you are missing the point.&nbsp;&nbsp;=)<br><br>Yes--anyone who has 255 cap is the same if they are the same class.  It is just easier for a ORG to max out his STR/STA then any other class.  That allows him or her to focus on obtaining items to raise other stats that aren't as high.<br><br>It is far more difficult for a DE to cap his STR /STA than it is a ORG, as the ORG started with approx double the STR of a DE and damn near double the STA (and please dont say its easy cuz all you need is a SHM to buff you--that is just plain silliness).  At the end of the day, DEs have terrible melee stats.  Many of you might not like reading that, but its the truth.  Perhaps write to Verant if you want to change it--I didnt make the stats up.  <br><br>Personally, I dont have a problem with it.  You make a DE, you know what you are getting--a very intelligent class that isnt ideal for melee.  The ORG/TRL is pretty much the opposite--a thick-as-a-brick class that is built for melee.<br><br>=)<br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
