	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101915050098966><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=101915050098966>RE: Feign Death</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=101915050098966#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>262 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 18th 1:27 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.85]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>FD is one of those spells that you will be immensely proud of when it works and get extremely frustrated when doesn&amp;#8217;t (especially back-to-back failures).&nbsp;&nbsp;It seems to be inconsistent to say the least, but, in general, it works more often than it fails.<br><br>My initial thoughts for your repeated failures were that maybe you aren't turning attack off.  I know that I did this WAY TOO MANY TIMES!!  =).  I think that you will fail every time without attack being off.  Perhaps the successful times you weren&amp;#8217;t attacking?  I&amp;#8217;m not sure, but it&amp;#8217;s something to consider.<br><br>If memory serves, I think my biggest problem when I was 30ish was fizzling.  I quickly realized the importance of maxing out my Abjuration skill after that.  If you don&amp;#8217;t have max / near max Abjuration skill, try casting Endure Cold on yourself or others as much as possible to bring it up.  That might help.<br>At the end of the day, FD is not fool proof and has two ways of failing.<br>The most typical way is when you receive the message '&lt;player1&gt; has fallen to the ground'.  This signifies that you have not feigned successfully, and the mob(s) will treat you as an alive enemy and carry on attacking. <br>The other cause of feign death failing was originally thought of as a bug but turned out to be Verant's way of showing 'nothing is certain'.  What happens is just before you go to feign death the mob launches an attack, whether through casting or melee, and as you feign the mob registers that you are dead, but it does not pull back on its swing or stop casting. The result of which is that it still hits you on the floor.  Upon learning that even though are &quot;dead&quot; you do in fact take damage, they are smart enough to realize you are still alive and they will restart their attack. The only way around this is timing, you have to try time your feign just after the mobs finishes its attack.  There is no you can skill raise which can affect this.<br>I have experienced, however, a FEW interesting scenarios, both of which took place in Burning Woods (&amp;#8220;BW&amp;#8221;).  A moldering gorilla agroed me while medding (I was soloing) &amp; I didn&amp;#8217;t want to fight at the moment (still a little too beat up to carry on).  I successfully FD&amp;#8217;ed (didn&amp;#8217;t fall to the ground, nor did hit appear that he hit me on the way down) against a non-caster MOB&amp;#8212;he continued to hit me.  I got up, Shadow Stepped away from his sorry arse, FDed AGAIN (again successful in my eyes&amp;#8212;he wasn&amp;#8217;t even near me to hit me, nor was he a casting MOB) &amp; he ran over &amp; started smacking the crap out of me again.  Needless to say, I felt like strangling the people at Verant for this one&amp;#8230;  =)<br>A similar scenario happened a few days later in BW again.  I have no explanation for that, nor does it make any sense to me, but it happened&amp;#8230;  <br><br>Anyways, hopefully that helps.<br><br>Perhaps Neptunis might also have some thoughts&amp;#8212;I&amp;#8217;m not sure&amp;#8230;  =)<br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
