	   <tr><td colspan=2>Alot of armor is buyable, but not buy able.&nbsp;&nbsp;Like I can't see paying 40k for an item, that's just me.  IMHO I think that Sentient is the best buy for an Orge SK.  Reason being, you already have your Hp's, but your sk package is now missing one important thing, Mana.  I can't tell you how much I appreciate our even limited spell capabillities.<br>As a dark elf I have a higher mana pool and then plus my sentient armor.  I was dueling the other day against a fellow sk, lvl 42 and Im 41.  She went oom on me, and I still had 3 bubs left.  She casted alot more than I did, but because I had all that at my disposal guess who won.  <br>Work on your mana and you should be fine, but don't forget about your dex, and agi.  Your str and sta should be fine, that's why I believe you should go with Sentient. Although more expensive than DF.  Just depends how you like to play really.  Sk's are pretty versatile.<br><br>Just incase you weren't wondering what's the better gear for a newbie sk, then I believe Blood Ember would be one of my more favorite picks.  Clickable FD, Rock on.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Apr  8 13:18:38 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
