	   <tr><td colspan=2>Comment I found about Leech-curse--kinda a bummer...<br><br>QUITE FRANKLY THE MOST WORTHLESS DISC THERE IS [Leechcurse], By Thrymm gorescream<br><br>This discipline is pathetic. There is no excuse for it. Granted shadow knights can do some considerable damage in a combat round. At any given 15 seconds, with a 2 handed weapon (like the epic) you will only get 6 shots in average. I ran a damage calculator and the average damage per a second on a level 60 shadow knight with a cloak of flames is just over 32 damage. So in that 15 seconds you MIGHT get back just under 500 hp with it (But I have yet to see it). My experiences have always been, Miss Miss, 8, 2, miss, your weapons stop glowing. Even on events where I have a 255 str, at my haste cap and every other ATK buff spell on me, this discipline is a let down. The truth is that SK melee damage is erratic, and most of the melee damage you do in a fight is in those 5 or 6 shots where you crack someone for double 150's. The chances of getting those high end scores in that 15 seconds is pretty small. If the reuse time was maybe 15 minutes, or the duration 2 minutes, I'd consider hot keying it. But as it is now, it&amp;#8217;s a giant waste of time and will never turn the tides in a fight as much as a 1501 harm touch will. I've even tested to see if a normal harmtouch and leechcurse would add up to more than the unholy aura in value. It didn't...<br><br><br>=(<br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
