	   <tr><td colspan=2>deckert,<br><br>first off i think you should keep all your skills maxed. one because it's fun, and two because it is useful to switch between 1h and 2h slashing especially.<br><br>i would say that you will more often than not use 1h and a shield. the reason i say this is that you will find that as an sk the thing you excel at most is taunting mobs of casters. the combo of spells, attk, taunt &amp; bash work brilliantly for this.<br><br>so in a group situation. you would best serve the group in most cases fighting 1-handed. <br><br>if you are in a situation where you are only expected to deal damage. 2h will prolly be the better way to go for you.<br><br>that said i would shoot for a real nice 1h slash weapon - i recommend the sporali defender. i LOVE mine, but others on here have a lot more experience than me so listen to them first ;-)<br><br>good luck<br><br>colinmarsh<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
