	   <a name=101716342310468></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101716342310468><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=101716342310468>Advice/Opinion on SK Race</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=101716342310468#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153688><span id=Scholar>colinmarsh</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>61 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Mar 26th 12:27 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I will say this about race for SK's and advice on stats. If you want to play an sk who is a great tank (damage absorber and dealer) than you want to be a troll or ogre. If you want to roleplay a dark elf - go ahead, erudite - same thing. It's all personal preference.<br><br>As regards tanking / pulling with a DE SK I do it all the time and will admit that in certain ways we are lacking in it. The biggest way is hit points where we fall behind ogres and trolls significantly.<br><br>However, it is my opinion that the best thing an SK can lend to a group is the ability to get aggro away from casters. No class does it better. We can make mobs hates us and want to kill us better than anyone - the combo of aggro-pulling spells like darkness and disease, plus taunt, plus bash is powerful.<br><br>I have also noticed that my DE SK seems to taunt better than a troll SK in my guild despite his being slighter higher lvl than me. I think it may be that i just cast more but I'm not sure.<br><br>So, DE SK's are fun to play IMHO. I don't really care if I don't dish out the damage that trolls do. I don't and from a pure damage dealing perspective they are much better. No question. But from a taunting perspective i think the DE is the best and that is what especially at high lvls, SK's offer to a group.<br><br>At high lvls people will want warriors as damage dealers. There is no comparison between warriors and sk's with regard to damage - regardless of race. I also play with a DE Warrior who hits MUCH harder than my SK - MUCH.<br><br>SK's are not really great damage dealers. They are great pullers after 30 with invis, feign death. And the best taunters. But if you want to purely tank - absorb damage and deal damage - a warrior is what you want.<br><br>If you chose a dark elf SK i would focus on stamina not dex or str. i focused on str. and later found a TON of str. enhancing items. as regards dex. it is important as it helps increase weapon skills. but i've managed to max all 5 weapon disciplines for my lvl without too much in the way of dex enhancing gear. you can still get them up with the lower dex.<br><br>I also have found that my interruption when casting is fine as long as i time my casting well by watching the text screen below so i don't think that is too hard to get past.<br><br>but stamina is REAL important. if you are an SK you will be expected to taunt aggro of casters which means hit points will play highly in your survival sta. enhancing gear is NOT common and when found EXPENSIVE. put points into stamina i think - be you DE or Erudite or Gnome. you WILL NOT regret it.<br><br>as regards armor i use the same principles - sta enhancing number one, followed by ac lvl. don't focus on str. enhancing dex enhancing at the expense of ac. ac is important. get str. high enough to where you can wear good armor. don't worry about it too much after that. the siphon str. spell at lvl 9 will help you there.<br><br>with the proc of my reaver , siphon str. and various gear my str. in battle is usually about 140 - pretty high for a DE and i still don't hit anywhere near as hard as any warrior or paladin. damage dealing just isn't that great for DE SK's doesn't mean the combo isn't a LOT of fun.<br><br>i will warn you as an SK of one of the weaker races - DE, Erudite, prolly Gnome, you will DIE ALOT. i guarantee it. especially before 30. you are hated and aggro'd more than folks around you and if you pull / tank like me you'll die an insane amount. it's all about what's fun for you. for me, i like pulling even if i die, it's just how i wish to roleplay my character.<br><br>anyway, hope my advice can help a few out there and wish folks could stop flaming one another and just state their opinions in a calm manner. anyway....<br><br>best of luck future sk's - of ALL races<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
