	   <tr><td colspan=2>iksar sk's<br><br>i will start this post by admitting that i have not ever played an iksar character and so don't know as much as many out there.<br><br>what i can say is this. if you like being kos - iksars are the race to be. they add a significant challenge in not being able to go into almost any cities.<br><br>the regen factor they have is very nice as well. i've noticed that some iksar monks in our guild regenerate hit points very quickly which i think would be a nice ability to have as an sk. your mana pool would be a bit smaller with lower intelligence, but there are tradeoffs with everything.<br><br>the 2 other things i have to say about iksar are not sk specific:<br><br>1. the armor issue - not being able to wear lots of plate armors can be a pain and the secondary market for armor you can wear tends to be expensive since folks know you have fewer choices. there is nice iksar armor out there it just tends to be a higher price than equivalent stuff for other races<br><br>2. the kos everywhere issue. while you may like roleplaying this and i know several others folks that do. most iksar players i know will silently confide to me that the lack of places to sell / bank is a real frustration point for them at times. that said many of these folks have iksar in the lvl 50 + range so, it's not undoable.<br><br>play what you like. iksar sk is not common and for that reason alone prolly a fun one to play.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
