	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree--IKS charaters are KOS almost everywhere, which poses quite a challenge sometimes.&nbsp;&nbsp; What's funny though, is that that same feature also yields some nice benefits.<br><br>Verant made the game so that an Iksar doesnt have to go far from home to get to level 60, since they are so hated everywhere.  In other words, there are enough zones in Kunark alone to go from lvl 1 to lvl 60 (if you wanted to), which is nice.  You don't have to travel the globe searching for places to hunt, begging for ports, etc...its all rite there if you want it.<br><br>Additionally, once you get 40ish, you can, if you want, leave Kunark &amp; safely make it to Luclin.  IKS are not KOS there.  Further, kill giants in Velious &amp; the dwarves will absolutely love you, so you can also bank/hunt there if desired also. It isnt too bad to me, but it might be if your expectations have been established from playing a HUM character or something.<br><br>Further, having everyone hate you can be totally cool.  Why do I say that?  Well, you can just hate em back--faction means crap to many IKS I know.  Who cares about faction if they hate you already?  BAH!!  HATE EM BACK!!  Dont worry about who you kill--you can go/do anything you want!!  =)  For instance, try planning a PoG raid &amp; find some CLRs to go with you.  It seems that 1/2 I meet worship Tunare (which is a major pain in the butt, because they wont head there &amp; kill faction    hehe).<br><br>I suppose that the King in Braveheart put it best<br><br>&quot;As King, you must find the good in any situation.&quot;<br><br>hehe<br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
